HEADWORD: Bose-Einstein statistics
<hw>Bo`se-Ein"stein sta*tis"tics</hw> <pr>(b⟦omac⟧`z⟦esl⟧
⟦imac⟧n"st⟦imac⟧n st⟦adot⟧*t⟦icr⟧s"t⟦icr⟧ks)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>
<ety>[From physicists S. N. <ets>Bose</ets>, and Albert
<ets>Einstein</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A law of
statistical mechanics which is obeyed by a system of particles when
interchange of two particles does not change the wave function.
Contrasted to <contr>Fermi-Dirac statistics</contr>. See also
<er>boson</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

